</taxonomicName>
. A, one specimen, scale bar = 1cm; B, siphon spines; C, gut loop.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3226557B95E3C03FF3B51D1BF103DF1" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B8736DCB95E3C03FF3B51D1BF103DF1" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
<taxonomicName id="4C384D5FB95E3C03FF3B51D1BB4D3DB9" box="[199,315,152,176]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Pyuridae" genus="Herdmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis id="B94CEACEB95E3C03FF3B51D1BB4D3DB9" box="[199,315,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">H. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was long confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D5FB95E3C03FD9D51D0B94E3DB9" baseAuthorityName="Savigny" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[609,824,152,176]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Pyuridae" genus="Herdmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="momus">
<emphasis id="B94CEACEB95E3C03FD9D51D0B94E3DB9" box="[609,824,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Herdmania momus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Full descriptions of this very common species have already been given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B2DB95E3C03FE6251F5B81B3DDD" box="[414,621,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" refId="ref9520" refString="Van Name, W. G. (1921) Ascidians of the West Indian region and Southeastern United States. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 44, 283 - 494." type="journal article">Van Name (1921)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B2DB95E3C03FD8751F4B9253DDD" box="[635,851,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" refId="ref8485" refString="Monniot, C. (1983) Ascidies littorales de Guadeloupe VI. Pyuridae et Molgulidae. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 5, A n ° 4, 1021 - 1044." type="journal article">Monniot C. (1983)</bibRefCitation>
for Western Atlantic specimens, and other records from Indian or Pacific Oceans are in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B2DB95E3C03FDC95197B9773DF1" box="[565,769,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" refId="ref8931" refString="Nishikawa, T. (2002) Revision of the Ascidian genus Herdmania (Urochordata, Ascidiacea) inhabiting Japanese waters. Japanese Society of Systematic zoology, 7, 217 - 250. https: // doi. org / 10.12782 / specdiv. 7.217" type="journal article">Nishikawa (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B2DB95E3C03FCF15197B9963DF1" box="[781,992,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" refId="ref8557" refString="Monniot, C. (2002) Stolidobranchia ascidians from the tropical Western Indian Ocean. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 135, 65 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1096 - 3642.2002.00017. x" type="journal article">Monniot C. (2002)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA94B2DB95E3C03FBEA5197BF173DF1" box="[1046,1377,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" refId="ref8816" refString="Monniot, F. &amp; Debitus, C. (2015) Redescription of Herdmania papietensis Herdman, 1882 (Ascidiacea, Pyuridae) from Polynesia. Zootaxa, 3911 (2), 294 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3911.2.11" type="journal article">Monniot F. &amp; Debitus (2015)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
